Hungarian Shares Gain Second Day as OTP Bank, Richter Advance

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-15T07:14:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/hungarian-shares-gain-second-day-as-otp-bank-richter-advance.html
Hungary’s equity index rose for a
second day as OTP Bank Nyrt., the country’s biggest lender, and
drugmaker Gedeon  Richter Nyrt . gained.  The BUX index of 13 companies rose 0.5 percent to 16,706.77
as of 9:11 a.m. in Budapest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
